  "prompt": "How to reset Honeywell thermostat and erase schedule?",
  "response": "The exact steps to reset your Honeywell thermostat and erase its schedule will vary slightly depending on the specific model you have. However, here's a general guide with instructions for the most common models, along with some troubleshooting tips:\n\n**1. Identify Your Thermostat Model:**\n\n*   **Look at the thermostat itself:** The model number is usually printed on the front, back, or side of the thermostat. You might need to remove the faceplate to see it. Common model prefixes include: T, RTH, TH, TL, YTH, CT.\n*   **Check the documentation:** If you still have the user manual or installation guide, the model number will be listed there.\n*   **Search online:** If you know some key features of your thermostat (e.g., touchscreen, Wi-Fi, programmable), you can try searching online using those keywords.\n\n**2. General Reset Methods (Try these first):**\n\n*   **Basic Power Cycle (Most Models):**\n    1.  **Turn off the breaker:** Locate the circuit breaker that controls your thermostat (it might be labeled \"HVAC\" or \"Thermostat\"). Turn the breaker to the \"off\" position.\n    2.  **Wait:** Leave the breaker off for at least 1 minute. This allows the thermostat to completely lose power and reset.\n    3.  **Turn on the breaker:** Turn the breaker back to the \"on\" position.\n    4.  **Check the thermostat:** The thermostat should restart. It might display a default screen or ask you to set the date and time. If that's the case, the schedule *may* be erased. If the schedule is still present, continue to the model-specific instructions.\n\n*   **Battery Removal (for Battery-Powered Models):**\n    1.  **Turn off the power:** If the thermostat has an on/off switch, turn it off.  Also, turn off the breaker.\n    2.  **Remove batteries:** Open the thermostat casing and remove the batteries.\n    3.  **Wait:** Leave the batteries out for at least 5 minutes.\n    4.  **Reinstall batteries:** Put the batteries back in.\n    5.  **Turn on the power:** Turn the thermostat back on (if applicable) and turn the breaker back on.\n\n**3. Model-Specific Reset Instructions (Most Common Models):**\n\nThese instructions assume that the above basic methods didn't work and that you still have the schedule.  If the thermostat prompted you for setup *after* you tried the power cycle, the schedule is likely gone and you can skip these.\n\n*   **For Touchscreen Models (e.g., T5, T6, T9, T10, Prestige IAQ):**\n    1.  **Menu:**  Press the \"Menu\" button (if present) or tap the screen to access the menu options.\n    2.  **Settings/Preferences:** Look for a \"Settings,\" \"Preferences,\" or \"Installer Setup\" option.\n    3.  **Reset:**  Within the settings, you should find a \"Reset Schedule,\" \"Factory Reset,\" or \"Clear Schedule\" option.  Select this option.\n    4.  **Confirmation:** The thermostat may ask you to confirm your selection. Follow the on-screen prompts to complete the reset.\n    5.  **Reconfigure:**  After the reset, you'll likely need to reconfigure your Wi-Fi settings, date, time, and any other preferences.\n\n*   **For Non-Touchscreen, Button-Based Models (e.g., RTH Series, TH Series):**\n    1.  **Hold Down Buttons:** Look for a combination of buttons that trigger a reset.  Common combinations include:\n        *   \"Hold\" + \"Up\" arrow simultaneously.\n        *   \"Run\" + \"Up\" arrow simultaneously.\n        *   \"Fan\" + \"Hold\" simultaneously.\n    2.  **Press and Hold:** Press and hold the button combination for about 10 seconds.\n    3.  **Look for Reset Confirmation:**  The screen might flash or display a message like \"Reset,\" \"Factory Reset,\" or a default code (e.g., \"0580\").\n    4.  **Installer Setup (Older Models):**  Some older models require you to enter an installer setup code to reset the schedule. To find the code, you might need to press the \"System\" or \"Fan\" button for several seconds. If a number appears on the screen, write it down. Then:\n        * Press the \"System\" button until \"Off\" appears.\n        * Press and hold the \"Up\" and \"Down\" arrow buttons simultaneously until the display changes to the installer setup menu.\n        * Use the \"Up\" and \"Down\" arrow buttons to scroll through the options until you find \"Reset to Factory Settings\" or similar.\n        * Select \"Yes\" or \"On\" to reset.\n\n*   **Honeywell Wi-Fi Thermostats (Lyric T5, T6, T9, T10, Smart Thermostat):**\n    1.  **Honeywell Home App:** The easiest way to reset a Wi-Fi thermostat is often through the Honeywell Home app (formerly Lyric).\n    2.  **Thermostat Settings:** Open the app, select your thermostat, and go to \"Settings.\"\n    3.  **Remove Device/Factory Reset:** Look for an option to \"Remove Thermostat,\" \"Factory Reset,\" or similar.  Removing the thermostat from the app will typically erase the schedule.\n    4.  **Confirmation:** The app will likely ask you to confirm.\n\n**4. Advanced Reset Methods (If the above fail):**\n\n*   **Installer Setup/Advanced Settings:** Some thermostats have a hidden \"Installer Setup\" or \"Advanced Settings\" menu where you can perform a more complete reset.  The method to access this varies, but often involves:\n    *   Pressing and holding the \"Fan\" and \"System\" buttons simultaneously for several seconds.\n    *   Pressing and holding the \"Up\" and \"Down\" arrow buttons simultaneously for several seconds.\n    *   Consult the user manual for your specific model.\n\n**Important Notes and Troubleshooting:**\n\n*   **Consult the User Manual:** Always refer to the user manual for your specific Honeywell thermostat model for the most accurate and detailed instructions.  You can usually find the manual online by searching for \"Honeywell [your model number] user manual.\"\n*   **Power Outages:** A prolonged power outage can sometimes corrupt the thermostat's memory, making a reset necessary.\n*   **Professional Help:** If you've tried all the above steps and your thermostat still isn't resetting or behaving correctly, consider contacting a qualified HVAC technician. There might be an underlying issue with the thermostat itself.\n*   **Wi-Fi/Connectivity:** If you're having trouble resetting a Wi-Fi thermostat, make sure your Wi-Fi network is working correctly and that the thermostat is within range of the router.\n*   **Firmware Updates:** Some Wi-Fi thermostats receive automatic firmware updates. Occasionally, an update can cause issues. Check if a recent update might be the cause of your problem.\n\n**After the Reset:**\n\n*   **Reprogram:** After the reset, you'll need to reprogram your desired temperature schedule.\n*   **Wi-Fi Setup:** If it's a Wi-Fi thermostat, you'll need to reconnect it to your Wi-Fi network.\n*   **Settings:** Reconfigure any other settings you had customized (e.g., date, time, display settings).\n\nBy following these steps and consulting your thermostat's user manual, you should be able to successfully reset your Honeywell thermostat and erase its schedule. Good luck!\n",
